<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 04 at 2:26AM CDT  by NWS Bismarck</headline>
<description>...STRONG THUNDERSTORMS WILL IMPACT PORTIONS OF SIOUX, SOUTHWESTERN
BURLEIGH, EASTERN MORTON AND WESTERN EMMONS COUNTIES THROUGH 300 AM
CDT...
At 225 AM CDT, strong thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 7 miles southwest of Lake Harmon to 8 miles northwest
of Solen to near Selfridge. Movement was northeast at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts to 50 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Mandan and Lake Harmon around 235 AM CDT.
Other locations in the path of these storms include Fort Yates and
Prairie Knights Resort.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 300 AM CDT for
south central North Dakota.</instruction>
